            <abstract id="ref1" label="Abstract">This volume was made at Wilmington, Delaware, for determining the longitude, from 1 July-14 October. It records the position of selected stars and planets. Contains also: Note regarding his astronomical clock, and entries relative to his work in continuing the Mason &amp; Dixon's line.</abstract>
