        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>David Rittenhouse was an instrument-maker, astronomer, and treasurer of Pennsylvania. Elected to the American Philosophical Society in 1768, he served as its president from 1791 to 1796.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <odd id="ref9">
            <head>Early American History Note</head>
            <p>This slender volume contains meteorological and some astronomical data taken at Wilmington, Delaware from July 1 to October 14, 1784. In addition to the data, the volume contains marginalia on the weather, his astronomical clock, and his calculations for finishing the Mason-Dixon Line.</p>
        </odd>
